# Deployment & Build Standards

## 12-Factor App Compliance

### I. Codebase
- One repo, many deploys (microservice mode and monolith mode from same repo)
- Feature branches for development; `release-*` branches for releases
- Never deploy uncommitted code

### II. Dependencies
- Backend: all dependencies declared in `pom.xml` with explicit versions; no system-scope JARs
- Frontend: all dependencies in `package.json` with locked versions in `package-lock.json`
- Never install global packages that the build depends on
- Run `npm ci` (not `npm install`) in CI/CD for reproducible builds

### III. Config
- Store config in environment variables, not in code
- Backend: `application.yml` uses `${ENV_VAR:default}` syntax for all external values
- Frontend: `process.env.REACT_APP_*` for all environment-specific values
- Secrets (DB passwords, JWT secrets, API keys) MUST come from env vars at runtime
- Never commit `.env.local`, `.env.production`, or any file containing real secrets
- Document all required env vars in `.env.example` with placeholder values

### IV. Backing Services
- Treat MySQL, Redis, Kafka, Eureka as attached resources configured via URLs
- Connection strings via env vars: `SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL`, `SPRING_KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP_SERVERS`
- Service URLs via env vars: `USER_SERVICE_URL`, `EXPENSE_SERVICE_URL`, etc.
- Swap backing services by changing env vars, not code

### V. Build, Release, Run
- Build: `mvn clean package` (backend), `npm run build` (frontend) -- produces artifacts
- Release: Docker image with config injected at runtime, not baked in
- Run: `docker-compose up` or Kubernetes deployment
- Never modify code in a running container

### VI. Processes
- Each microservice is a stateless process
- Session state in Redis, not in-process memory
- File uploads stored externally (S3 or equivalent), not on local disk
- WebSocket connections managed by Spring + SockJS/STOMP with external session store

### VII. Port Binding
- Each service binds its own port via `server.port` in `application.yml`
- Ports are environment-configurable: `${SERVER_PORT:6000}`
- Frontend served by Nginx on port 80 inside container

### VIII. Concurrency
- Scale horizontally by running multiple instances behind Gateway/load balancer
- Kafka consumers support concurrency via `concurrency` property in `@KafkaListener`
- No in-memory shared state between instances

### IX. Disposability
- Services start fast (Spring Boot startup < 30s target)
- Graceful shutdown: handle SIGTERM, finish in-flight requests
- Kafka consumers commit offsets cleanly on shutdown

### X. Dev/Prod Parity
- `docker-compose.yml` replicates production topology locally
- `monolithic-service` + `docker-compose.monolith.yml` for simplified local dev
- Same JDK version (17) in dev and production
- Same MySQL version in dev Docker and production

### XI. Logs
- Treat logs as event streams -- write to stdout/stderr
- No file-based logging in production containers
- Use `@Slf4j` everywhere; log format includes timestamp, level, service name
- Log aggregation handled by infrastructure (ELK/CloudWatch), not application

### XII. Admin Processes
- Database migrations as part of deployment pipeline, not manual scripts
- One-off tasks via Spring `@Scheduled` or dedicated admin endpoints behind auth
- Admin panel (`features/admin/`) protected by `ROLE_ADMIN`

## Docker Standards

### Backend Dockerfile Pattern

```dockerfile
FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jre-alpine
WORKDIR /app
COPY target/*.jar app.jar
EXPOSE ${PORT}
ENTRYPOINT ["java", "-jar", "app.jar"]
```

Rules:
- Use `jre-alpine` (not full JDK) for smaller images
- Never copy source code into production image
- Never bake secrets into image layers
- Set `ENTRYPOINT`, not `CMD`, for proper signal handling

### Frontend Dockerfile Pattern

```dockerfile
FROM node:20-alpine AS build
WORKDIR /app
COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm ci
COPY . .
RUN npm run build

FROM nginx:alpine
COPY --from=build /app/build /usr/share/nginx/html
COPY nginx.conf /etc/nginx/conf.d/default.conf
EXPOSE 80
```

Rules:
- Multi-stage build: node for build, nginx for serve
- `npm ci` for deterministic installs
- SPA routing: `try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html` in nginx.conf
- Static assets: long cache (`1y`), `index.html`: no-cache

## CI/CD Standards (Jenkins)

- `mvn clean package` with parallel service builds
- Skip tests in build stage only if running tests in a separate stage
- Tag Docker images with git commit SHA or build number, not `latest`
- Automated artifact collection to known location

## Pre-Deployment Checks

### Backend
- [ ] `mvn clean package` succeeds without errors
- [ ] No `System.out.println` in codebase
- [ ] All `application.yml` values use `${ENV_VAR:default}` for external resources
- [ ] No hard-coded localhost URLs in non-default profiles
- [ ] Kafka topic names are constants, not string literals scattered in code
- [ ] Actuator endpoints disabled or secured
- [ ] CORS origins configured, no wildcard in production profile
- [ ] Health check endpoint (`/actuator/health`) enabled and returns 200

### Frontend
- [ ] `npm run build` succeeds without errors or warnings
- [ ] No `console.log` or `debugger` in committed code
- [ ] All env vars documented in `.env.example`
- [ ] No `http://localhost:*` URLs in committed code (only in env defaults)
- [ ] Bundle size checked (no unexpected large dependencies)
- [ ] nginx.conf has proper SPA routing and cache headers
- [ ] Source maps disabled or not shipped to production

### Both
- [ ] `.gitignore` excludes: `node_modules/`, `target/`, `.env.local`, `*.log`, `.idea/`
- [ ] No secrets in committed code (grep for passwords, tokens, keys)
- [ ] Docker images build successfully
- [ ] `docker-compose up` starts all services without errors
